      "writtenOn": "2026-04-09T10:24:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am not sure about this.\n\nDo we want to remove the preserved packfile based on when it was _placed_ into the `preserved` directory or based on its _age_ (as in, when it was created)?\n\nImagine we have an old packfile in `object/pack` with these stats:\n\n```\nstat -f \"atime: %Sa%nmtime: %Sm%nctime: %Sc%nbirth: %SB\" pack-123.pack\natime: Feb 27 12:25:04 2026\nmtime: Feb 27 12:25:04 2026\nctime: Feb 27 12:25:04 2026\nbirth: Feb 27 12:25:04 2026\n```\n\nThen we run\n\n```\njgit-7.0.0.sh gc --preserve-oldpacks\n```\n\nNow the `preserved` directory is created and the packfile is moved into it.\nIf we look at the stats of the preserved packfile we now get:\n\n```\nstat -f \"atime: %Sa%nmtime: %Sm%nctime: %Sc%nbirth: %SB\" pack-123.old-pack\natime: Feb 27 12:25:04 2026\nmtime: Feb 27 12:25:04 2026\nctime: Apr  9 12:11:30 2026 \u003c--- !!!\nbirth: Feb 27 12:25:04 2026\n```\n\nNote how only the metadata of the file changed (the `ctime`). `mtime` stays the same, because the _content_ of the file is the same.\n\nIf we prune the preserved directory based on `modification time`, we are likely going to target preserved packfiles that will **immediately** qualify for removal: \n\nSince they are in the preserved directory chances are that they were created more than 2 hours ago, for example.\n\nShould we not apply the prunePreservedExpire on the time _they were preserved_, rather than the time they were `created`?\n\nEither way I think this should be documented properly.\n\nThoughts?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 106,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 106,
        "endChar": 78
      },
      "revId": "8db3b67a5fa26c3d49814a7d5a6403ee6de7ea6a",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
